data.title: Musicians born on July 29
data.meta_description: List of musicians who were born on July 29
data.text:
Born on July 29

Country singer Ashley McBryde is born in Waldron, Arkansas. She drops out of college and starts playing bars in 2002 but doesn't break through until 2017 when she lands a record deal and releases her first single, "A Little Dive Bar In Dahlonega."

Wanya Morris (of Boyz II Men) is born in Philadelphia, Pennsylvania.

Chris Gorman (drummer for Belly) is born in Buffalo, New York.

Country singer Martina McBride is born in Sharon, Kansas.

John Sykes (guitarist for Whitesnake, Thin Lizzy) is born in Reading, Berkshire, England.

Rush frontman Geddy Lee is born Geddy Lee Weinrib in Willowdale, Ontario, Canada.

Patti Scialfa (Bruce Springsteen's E Street Band) is born in Deal, New Jersey.

Carlo Paul Santanna (lead singer of Paper Lace) is born in the UK to an Italian mother and Polish father.

Neal Doughty (keyboardist for REO Speedwagon) is born in Evansville, Indiana.

Randy Sparks (of The New Christy Minstrels) is born in Leavenworth, Kansas.

Austro-Hungarian composer Sigmund Romberg is born Siegmund Rosenberg in Nagykanizsa, Hungary.
